docs.abstract: Erica Garner, a prominent campaigner against police brutality after her father’s death, was placed in a medically induced coma after a heart attack.
docs.snippet: Erica Garner, a prominent campaigner against police brutality after her father’s death, was placed in a medically induced coma after a heart attack.
docs.lead_paragraph: The oldest daughter of Eric Garner, the black man whose dying calls of “I can’t breathe” after he was placed in a chokehold by a police officer became a protest chant across the country, has been hospitalized after a heart attack, her mother said on Monday.

headline.main: Eric Garner’s 27-Year-Old Daughter Is in a Coma
headline.print_headline: Garner’s Daughter Is in Coma After Having a Heart Attack

docs.abstract: Ms. Garner, whose father died in 2014 after being put in a police chokehold, was a prominent critic of policing tactics.
docs.snippet: Ms. Garner, whose father died in 2014 after being put in a police chokehold, was a prominent critic of policing tactics.
docs.lead_paragraph: Erica Garner, the daughter of Eric Garner who became an outspoken activist against police brutality after her father’s death at the hands of a New York police officer, died on Saturday, according to her mother. She was 27.

headline.main: Erica Garner, Activist and Daughter of Eric Garner, Dies at 27
headline.print_headline: Erica Garner, Who Fought  Police Brutality, Dies at 27
